{"lemma":"سَلامٌ","slug":"سَلامٌ","root":"س.ل.م","root_slug":"س-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَلام","root":"سلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":42},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["intj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20546","n20547"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَلِمَ (salima) (form I), well-being","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"peace"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"greeting"},{"pos":"intj","gloss":"salutation; greeting"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَالَمَ (sālama) (form III)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of variety of سَلِم (salim, “stones”), or alternative collective","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of variety of سَلَْم (salam, “Vachellia flava”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Semantic loan from Aramaic שְׁלָמָא / ܫܠܵܡܵܐ (šəlāmā, “wholeness, welfare; peace”, used as a greeting). Cognate with Hebrew שלום (shalóm)."},"ipa":["/sa.laːm/","/si.laːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20546","headword_ar":"سَلَامٌ","root":"slm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) in its primary acceptation, (TA,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmapN","text_ar":"سَلَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,) as is also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamN","text_ar":"سَلَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, [so in one of my copies, but omitted in the other copy,]) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Safety, security, immunity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom, from faults, defects, imperfections, blemishes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vices,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * [mentioned in one only of my two copies, and there as relating peculiarly to the third word,] K, [in which it ostensibly relates peculiarly to the first word, but in the CK, by the omission of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"before it, it is made to relate only to the second word,] and TA, [accord. to which it relates to the first and second words, as it is well known to do,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and from evils of any kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safety, security, immunity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"freedom;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmapN","text_ar":"سَلَامَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, M:) IKt says that these two words may be dial. vars. [syn. each with the other]; or the former may be pl. of the latter [or rather a coll. gen. n. of which the latter is the n. un.]: (M, TA:) and Suh says, in the R, that most of the lexicologists hold them to have one [and the same] meaning: but that if they considered the language of the Arabs, and the distinction, or limitation, denoted by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", they would see that between them is a great difference [inasmuch as the former has a large range of meaning which the latter has not, as will be seen from what follows]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayokumo","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an announcement of the continuance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmap","text_ar":"سَلَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or safety, &c.]: (Bd in xiii. 24:) [it may therefore be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light and abide, on you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, generally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peace be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light and abide, on you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nothing disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, shall befall you henceforth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 34:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayoka","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[may be rendered in like manner; for it virtually] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do to thee anything that is disliked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xix. 48;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor say to thee henceforward what would annoy thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be disagreeable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd ibid.) It may also be [rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peace, be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light and abide, on you;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as] a prayer for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmap","text_ar":"سَلَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", to those to whom it is addressed, from the state in which they are at the time. (Bd in xxviii. 55.) [It is generally held that this salutation may not be used by, nor to, any but a Muslim.] In the beginning of an epistle, the approved practice is to write"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in repeating it, at the end, to write it with that article. (Durrat el-Ghowwás, in De Sacy's Anthol. Gramm. Arabe, p. 72 of the Arabic text. [In the latter case, the general practice in the present day is to write simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~alaAm","text_ar":"وَالسَّلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", suppressing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) In saluting the dead, one puts"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"first, saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka salaAmu A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ سَلَامُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 367.) You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAna ka*aA waka*aA","text_ar":"مَا كَانَ كَذَا وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA bisalaAmatika","text_ar":"لَا بِسَلَامَتِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No, by thy safety, such and such things were not"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ulaAmu","text_ar":"السُّلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,) [applied to Him in the Kur lix. 23, accord. to some for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw Als~alaAmi","text_ar":"ذُو السَّلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw Als~alaAmapi","text_ar":"ذُو السَّلَامَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] because of his safety, or freedom, from defect, and imperfection, and cessation of existence; (IKt, M, TA;) or from variations, and as being the everlasting, who brings the creation to nought and will not come to nought; or, accord. to Suh in the R, He is so named [as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Author of Safety, Security,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; i. e.] because He has rendered all his creatures safe, or free, from defectiveness, or unsoundness, and mankind and the jinn, or genii, from the betiding of injustice, or wrong, to them, from Him; and the expositors who assert that He is thus named because of his safety, or freedom, from imperfections, and evils of any kind, utter an unseemly saying, making"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be syn. with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAlimN","text_ar":"سَالِمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter applies only to him who is liable to evil of any kind, and who expects it, and then becomes safe, or free, from it. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAru Als~alaAmi","text_ar":"دَارُ السَّلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) [applied thereto in the Kur vi. 127 and x. 26,] as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the abode of everlasting safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, M, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the abode of safety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"security, from evils of any kind, from death and decrepitude and diseases"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the abode of God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silomN","text_ar":"سِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b3-  [As is there stated,] it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Salutation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greeting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) particularly the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"salutation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_isolaAm","text_ar":"الاـِسْلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayoka","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayokumo","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. above]; (Bd in iv. 96;) a subst. (S, Mgh, Msb, TA) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sal~ama","text_ar":"سَلَّمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [i. e.] from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~usoliymu","text_ar":"التُّسْلِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmN","text_ar":"كَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~akoliymu","text_ar":"التَّكْلِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh. [See 2, third sentence.]) ―         -b4-  In the saying in the Kur [xxv. 64],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA xaATabahumu A@lojaAhiluwna qaAluwA salaAmFA","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا خَاطَبَهُمُ ا@لْجَاهِلُونَ قَالُوا سَلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when the ignorant speak to them, they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmFA","text_ar":"سَلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"], this last word signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~umFA","text_ar":"تَسَلُّمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~umFA minokumo","text_ar":"تَسَلُّمًا مِنْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"natasal~amu minokumo tasal~umFA","text_ar":"نَتَسَلَّمُ مِنْكُمْ تَسَلُّمًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We declare ourselves to be clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, of you"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaArakahF lalumo","text_ar":"مُتَارَكَهً لَلُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nutaArikukumo mutaArakapF","text_ar":"نُتَارِكُكُمْ مُتَارَكَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we relinquish you"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Bd,) [and means]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there shall be neither good nor evil between us"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, M, Bd)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and you:"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"slAm","text_ar":"سلام"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is used in salutation; for the verse was revealed at Mekkeh, and the Muslims had not then been commanded to salute the believers in a plurality of gods: (Sb, M:) [in iv. 88 of the Kur, which was promulgated afterwards, at ElMedeeneh, is a general command to return a salutation with a better or with the same; but the Sunneh prescribes that the salutation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayokumo","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when addressed to a Muslim by one not a Muslim is to be returned only by saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEalayoka","text_ar":"وَعَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEalayokumo","text_ar":"وَعَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or the meaning in xxv. 64 is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they say a right saying, in which they are secure from harming and sinning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) Sb asserts that Aboo-Rabee'ah used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA laqiyta","text_ar":"اـِذَا لَقِيتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA faqulo salaAmFA","text_ar":"فُلَانًا فَقُلْ سَلَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~umFA","text_ar":"تَسَلُّمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atasal~amu minoka","text_ar":"اَتَسَلَّمُ مِنْكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasal~umFA","text_ar":"تَسَلُّمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When thou meetest such a one, say, I declare myself to be clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, of thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and he says that some of them said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The case of me and thee is the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being clear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quit, each of the other;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mutual relinquishing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [It is usual, in the present day, to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AifoEalo ka*aA waAls~alaAm","text_ar":"اِفْعَلْ كَذَا وَالسَّلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou such a thing, and there will be an end of altercation"},{"kind":"text","text":"between us.]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliymN","text_ar":"سَلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of trees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K;) they assert that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they are evergreen; nothing eats them; but the gazelles keep to them, and protect themselves by their shade, but do not hide among them; and they are not great trees, nor of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiDaAh","text_ar":"عِضَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn, M:) they are also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silaAmN","text_ar":"سِلَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamapN","text_ar":"سَلَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salamN","text_ar":"سَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which is of another kind; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAmN","text_ar":"اـِكَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akamapN","text_ar":"اَكَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IB, TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaAmu Ealayoka","text_ar":"السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was said to an Arab of the desert; and he replied,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljavojaAvu Ealayoka","text_ar":"الجَثْجَاثُ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and being asked, “ What is this reply? ” he answered, “ They are two bitter trees: thou hast put upon me one, so I have put upon thee the other. ” (K.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salimN","text_ar":"سَلِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Sb","M","Msb","Mgh","Bd","AHn","IB"]},{"entry_id":"n20547","headword_ar":"سِلَامٌ","root":"slm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salimN","text_ar":"سَلِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:       -A2-  and the paragraph here next preceding, last sentence but two."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85/","headword_ar":"سلام","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23317#0951de","body_html":"<span>السلام: تجرد النفس عن المحنة في الدارين. </span>"}]}}